definition.value: A poly(ether) polymer, composed of polyglycidol macromolecules.
A mannotetrose comprising four D-mannose residues joined by alpha-(1->2)-, alpha-(1->6)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
A poly(ether) polymer, composed of poly[4-(4-benzoylphenoxy)phenol] macromolecules.
A linear tetrasaccharide in which four mannopyranose residues are joined by alpha-(1->2)-, alpha-(1->2)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
A linear mannopentaose comprising five D-mannose residues joined by sequential alpha-(1->2)-, alpha-(1->2)-, alpha-(1->2)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
A mannopentaose consisting of five D-mannopyranose residues linked by four alpha-(1->2)-linkages.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion that results from the removal of four protons from the phosphate groups of fluoroacetyl-CoA. Protonated to pH 7.3.
A linear pentasaccharide comprising one glucose (at the reducing end) and four mannose residues joined by sequential alpha-(1->6)-, alpha-(1->2)-, alpha-(1->2)- and alpha-(1->2)-linkages.
A D-glucosyl-D-mannose with the two components joined by an alpha-(1->6)-linkage.
A tetrapeptide comprising L-alanyl, gamma-D-glutamyl, L-lysyl and D-alanine residues coupled in sequence.
An N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosaminide having phenyl as the anomeric substituent.
A cholesteryl glycoside having any 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactopyranosyl substituent attached at position 3 of cholesterol via a glycosidic linkage.
Any N-acetyl-D-glucosaminide having beta-configuration at the anomeric centre.
An N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminide having phenyl as the anomeric substituent.
A glycopentaosylceramide having alpha-D-Gal-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-D-Glc as the pentasaccharide component.
A cholesteryl 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactoside having oleoyl as the 6-O-acyl group.

A branched amino tetrasaccharide comprising N-acetyl-D-galactosamine at the reducing end with a N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1->3)-[alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 3-position.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising the linear sequence alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal with an additional beta-D-Glc residue attached to the GlcNAc at the 6-position.
A thiazolidinemonocarboxylic acid having the carboxy group at the 4-position and four additional methyl substituents at positions 2, 2, 5 and 5.
A poly(vinyl) polymer, composed of poly(vinyl butyral) macromolecules.
A poly(vinyl) polymer, composed of poly(acrylonitrile) macromolecules.
A poly(vinyl) polymer, composed of poly(vinylcarbazole) macromolecules.
A poly(vinyl) polymer, composed of poly(N-vinylimidazole) macromolecules.
A poly(vinyl) polymer, composed of polystyrene macromolecules.
A glycohexaosylceramide having beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycohexaosyl component.

A ten-membered fucosyl oligoglycosylceramide having alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the oligoglycosyl component.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-monophosphate that is adenosine 5'-monophosphate in which one of the hydroxy groups of the phosphate has been condensed with the carboxylic acid group of L-serine.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of Co-A with the carboxylic acid group of fluoroacetic acid.
A cholesteryl 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactoside having palmitoyl (hexadecanoyl) as the 6-O-acyl group.
A glycoheptaosylceramide having alpha-L-Fuc-(1->2)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->3)-beta-D-Gal-(1->4)-beta-D-Glc as the glycoheptaosyl component.
A cholesteryl 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactoside having decanoyl as the 6-O-acyl group.

A polysaccharide derivative composed of a backbone of beta-D-galactopyranuronosyl-(1->3)-2-acetamido-4-amino-2,4,6-trideoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-galactopyranurosyl repeating units that are joined to each other via (1->3)-linkages.
A cholesteryl 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactoside having hexanoyl as the 6-O-acyl group.
A cholesteryl 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactoside having acetyl as the 6-O-acyl group.

A polysaccharide phosphate composed of a backbone of tetrasaccharide-ribitol repeating units that are linked to each other by a phosphodiester linkage between position 5 of a D-ribitol residue and position 6 of a beta-D-glucopyranosyl residue.
A cholesteryl 6-O-acyl-beta-D-galactoside having 15-(ethyldisulfanyl)pentadecanoyl as the 6-O-acyl group.
Any saponin derived from a hydroxysteroid.
A steroid glycoside in which the steroid component is cholesterol.
A beta-D-galactoside comprising methyl beta-D-galactoside having a 15-(ethyldisulfanyl)pentadecanoyl group attached at the 6-position.
A beta-D-galactoside comprising phenyl beta-D-galactoside having a 15-(ethyldisulfanyl)pentadecanoyl group attached at the 6-position.
An anion resulting from the removal of a proton from an organic sulfamic acid group.
A dTDP-sugar having 4-acetamido-4,6-dideoxy-D-galactose as the sugar portion.
An organophosphate anion resulting from deprotonation of at least one of the acidic hydroxy groups from the triphosphate moiety of a 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate.
A glycosylmannose consisting of two alpha-D-mannopyranose residues joined via a (1->3)-linkage.
A xylose phosphate that is 3-O-(6-O-phosphono-alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-alpha-D-mannopyranose in which the dihydrogen phosphate group is condensed with the anomeric hydroxy group of alpha-D-xylose.
An organophosphate oxoanion that results from the removal of a proton from the phosphate group of 3-O-(6-O-alpha-D-xylosylphospho-alpha-D-mannopyranosyl)-alpha-D-mannopyranose.
Any benzoate anion carrying one or more amido substituents.
Any D-hexose 6-phosphate in which the hexose is in the pyranose form.
